b'Interested in how to best navigate a jobfair, improve your elevator pitch, or improve your\xc2\xa0communication skills on the job?'
b'Check out the recently added Navigating a Job Fair module, now with sound!\xc2\xa0 (see below for access directions)\xc2\xa0 Additionally all the career modules now have sound!'
b'Want to build other skills?\xc2\xa0 Current UIC Students can enroll in the Career Readiness 101 online learning series\xc2\xa0(stored on Blackboard) which equips students with the tools they need to launch and sustain successful careers.\xc2\xa0 You will find 5 mini online courses focused on various components of the internship/job search and the all-important first year on the job.\xc2\xa0 Each course is 15 minutes or less in duration and can be viewed online at your convenience!'
b'Career Readiness 101 online learning series'
b'\nHow to Access the Learning Modules'
b'http://bit.ly/uiccareerready'
b'Note: The online learning series is accessible only for UIC students with access to Blackboard.'
b'\xc2\xa0'
b'Course Modules Descriptions'
b"Navigating a Job Fair\nHoping to make a great first impression at a job fair?\xc2\xa0 Don't leave the house until you've reviewed this module so you can stand out from the competition!"
b'Mastering the Elevator Pitch\nDo you know how to deliver a winning elevator pitch?\xc2\xa0 Do you even know what one is?\xc2\xa0 Check out this module to find out how 60 seconds can impact the rest of your life!\n'
b'From Intern to Full-Time Employee: Making the Most of Your Internship\nSo you finally landed an internship--congratulations!\xc2\xa0 Did you know many organizations extend full-time offers to interns upon graduation?\xc2\xa0 How can you increase your chances of being one of them?\xc2\xa0 Check out this module for tips about making the best impression and increasing your chances of becoming a full-time employee.\n'
b'Workplace Communication: Overcoming Barriers to Thrive in Your Internship or Entry-level Job\nCommunication can be challenging, even in a social setting, but in the workplace it can be especially problematic.\xc2\xa0 View this video to learn how to communicate effectively, leading to good work relationships and a healthy environment.'
b'Your First Year on the Job\nSo you sweated through years of study and finally got a full-time job offer--congratulations!\xc2\xa0 All of that hard work has finally paid off.\xc2\xa0 But now is not the time to take it easy!\xc2\xa0 Your first year on the job is a transition period where everyone at the organization will be watching you closely.\xc2\xa0 View this video to learn ways to make sure your first year is a successful one.'
b'\nQuestions?'
b'Please contact the UIC Career Services Office at (312) 996-2300 for questions or to schedule an advising appointment.\xc2\xa0 Students may also drop in for 15-minute advising appointments during walk-in hours\xc2\xa0.'
